member.remarks:

It can be the name of an implemented function or explicit javascript statement(s).  If the name of the function is used, then that event handler may contain 3 parameters.

1st parameter contains reference to the TextEdit object.

2nd parameter contains instant text that appears in the editor.

3rd parameter contains reference to the ig_EventObject object.
            <p class="note">Note: 3rd parameter can be used to get a reference to the html element involved in the event.


var src = oEvent.srcElement;

var type = oEvent.srcType;

alert("tag of src=" + src.tagName + " type=" + type);

// possible values of type:

// -1 - editing field which is the INPUT element

// 0 - custom button which is the TD element

// 1 - upper spin button which is the TD element

// 2 - lower spin button which is the TD element
            </p>

